title: How can beginners install LED strips by themselves? #source #home#tutorial
description:
First, gather these: LED strips, power adapter, wire cutters.

"Key point: Check if the LED strip has a 'scissors mark'? You can only cut at the marked points, or the lights won’t work!"

"Peel off the adhesive backing like a sticky note—stick as you go! Don’t rip off the entire strip at once! If you mess up, you can redo it, but not too many times, or the adhesive will lose its stickiness!"

"Connecting the power is super easy! Align the positive and negative terminals on the connector, and click—it’s securely locked in!"
